commit.message:
Stop exporting resnet50.py

resnet50.py contains old implementation, and it is actually silently cover the new implementation which we want to export in resnet.py.

This should fix the confusion in https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/33459.

commit.message:
EfficientNet Implementation (#113)

* Re-implementation of EfficientNet architecture

* Fixed pre-processing

* Use standard decode_predictions

The order of labels is the same, so no need for a separate label map and function.

* Added import for EfficientNet in package root

* Added weights path and hashes for EfficientNet

* Unit test for EfficientNet

* Minor fix

* Added performance of EfficientNet to README.md

* Implemented drop connect

* Adjusted kernel_initializer of final dense layer
to match that of the reference implementation

* Handle request of non-existent pre-trained weights

* Use built-in keras initializers for EfficientNet

* PEP-8 conformity of EfficientNet module

* Fixed broadcasting of SE coefficients with Theano

* Corrected a comment

* Added weights for EfficientNet-B4 and -B5

* Removed global mean tensor from pre-processing

Backported from upstream (see https://github.com/keras-team/keras-applications/pull/121)

* New weights for EfficientNet B0-B7 trained with AutoAugment

* PEP-8 conformity

* Updated hashes of EfficientNet weights

* Removed error message for missing EfficientNet weights

* Disabled test of EfficientNet-B7 since it is too heavy for Travis

* Disabled test of EfficientNet-B6 since it might be too heavy for Travis

* Replace the custom preprocess_input as the standard one

* Make the hashes concise

* Replace the BlockArgs as a plain dict

* Keras-like style fixes

* Specify output_shape of broadcasting layer for Theano

* Minor style fixes

* Fix the discrepancy over backends
